Yeah.

1589
01:54:56,305 --> 01:55:01,811
Due respect to the Coliseum,
but this is a ballpark.

1590
01:55:01,977 --> 01:55:03,979
Yes, it is.

1591
01:55:06,065 --> 01:55:08,317
We're gonna have some lunch
in a little bit.

1592
01:55:08,484 --> 01:55:10,736
Why don't I have some coffee
sent up?

1593
01:55:11,404 --> 01:55:13,155
Denise?

1594
01:55:17,785 --> 01:55:19,662
Thank you, Denise.

1595
01:55:19,829 --> 01:55:21,872
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

1596
01:55:24,834 --> 01:55:28,504
You know, it's her birthday
and I need to get her a present...

1597
01:55:28,671 --> 01:55:31,632
but she's usually the one
that does that for me.

1598
01:55:32,341 --> 01:55:34,677
So do you have any ideas?

1599
01:55:35,219 --> 01:55:36,595
Scarf.

1600
01:55:36,762 --> 01:55:38,222
You mean like wool?

1601
01:55:38,389 --> 01:55:43,352
No, I meant what women wear with...
You know, decorative.

1602
01:55:43,727 --> 01:55:46,522
And where would I get something
like that?

1603
01:55:47,481 --> 01:55:50,818
No disrespect, I just lost in five
for the second year in a row.

1604
01:55:50,985 --> 01:55:53,320
Get her a bowling ball for all I care.

1605
01:55:53,487 --> 01:55:54,864
Right.

1606
01:55:55,781 --> 01:55:59,326
Well, Steve told me he's offering you
a new contract.

1607
01:56:00,786 --> 01:56:02,496
Yes.

1608
01:56:02,663 --> 01:56:05,332
So why did you return my call?

1609
01:56:07,418 --> 01:56:10,004
Because it's the Red Sox.

1610
01:56:10,171 --> 01:56:14,717
Because I believe science might offer
an answer to the Curse of the Bambino.

1611
01:56:15,384 --> 01:56:20,681
- Because I hear you hired Bill James.
- Yup.

1612
01:56:20,848 --> 01:56:25,561
You know, why someone took so long
to hire that guy is beyond me.

1613
01:56:26,520 --> 01:56:28,856
Well, baseball hates him.

1614
01:56:29,398 --> 01:56:34,111
Well, baseball can hate him,
you know.

1615
01:56:34,278 --> 01:56:38,240
One of the great things about money
is that it buys a lot of things...

1616
01:56:38,407 --> 01:56:41,952
one of which is the luxury
to disregard what baseball likes...

1617
01:56:42,119 --> 01:56:45,080
doesn't like, what baseball thinks,
doesn't think.

1618
01:56:47,374 --> 01:56:49,335
Sounds nice.

1619
01:56:52,087 --> 01:56:54,131
Well, I was grateful for the call.

1620
01:56:54,298 --> 01:56:56,175
- You were grateful?
- Yeah.

1621
01:56:59,428 --> 01:57:03,307
For 41 million,
you built a play-off team.

1622
01:57:03,474 --> 01:57:07,770
You lost Damon, Giambi,
Isringhausen, Peña...

1623
01:57:08,229 --> 01:57:11,607
and you won more games
without them than you did with them.

1624
01:57:11,774 --> 01:57:15,194
You won the exact same number
of games that the Yankees won...

1625
01:57:15,361 --> 01:57:19,281
but the Yankees spent 1 .4 million
per win...

1626
01:57:19,448 --> 01:57:22,910
and you paid 260,000.

1627
01:57:23,077 --> 01:57:27,122
I know you're taking it in the teeth,
but the first guy through the wall...

1628
01:57:27,581 --> 01:57:29,750
he always gets bloody.

1629
01:57:29,917 --> 01:57:33,295
Always. This is threatening
not just a way of doing business...

1630
01:57:33,462 --> 01:57:36,006
but in their minds,
it's threatening the game.

1631
01:57:36,173 --> 01:57:39,468
Really, what it's threatening
is their livelihood, their jobs.

1632
01:57:39,635 --> 01:57:42,638
It's threatening the way
that they do things.

1633
01:57:42,805 --> 01:57:44,181
Every time that happens...

1634
01:57:44,348 --> 01:57:47,851
whether it's a government,
a way of doing business, whatever...

1635
01:57:48,018 --> 01:57:50,563
the people
who are holding the reins...

1636
01:57:50,729 --> 01:57:53,315
they have their hands
on the switch...

1637
01:57:53,482 --> 01:57:55,985
they go batshit crazy.

1638
01:57:56,986 --> 01:58:01,824
I mean, anybody who's not
tearing their team down right now...

1639
01:58:01,991 --> 01:58:05,119
and rebuilding it
using your model...

1640
01:58:05,995 --> 01:58:07,830
they're dinosaurs.

1641
01:58:08,414 --> 01:58:12,835
They'll be sitting on their ass
on the sofa in October...

1642
01:58:13,002 --> 01:58:16,505
watching the Boston Red Sox
win the World Series.

1643
01:58:21,885 --> 01:58:23,804
What's this?

1644
01:58:23,971 --> 01:58:27,474
I want you to be my general manager.
That's my offer.

1645
01:59:14,396 --> 01:59:15,898
Heads up.

1646
01:59:17,566 --> 01:59:18,567
What was that?

1647
01:59:19,818 --> 01:59:22,905
- Sorry. I don't know.
- What the hell was that?

1648
01:59:23,572 --> 01:59:25,908
You knucklehead.

1649
01:59:33,415 --> 01:59:34,750
How was Boston?

1650
01:59:36,293 --> 01:59:38,212
Impressive.

1651
01:59:44,635 --> 01:59:47,262
Did Henry make you a good offer,
at least?

1652
01:59:48,806 --> 01:59:51,892
- Doesn't matter. Doesn't matter.
- What was it? What was it?

1653
01:59:52,059 --> 01:59:53,686
- Doesn't matter.
- What was it?

1654
02:00:16,750 --> 02:00:20,254
That makes you the highest-paid GM
in the history of sports.

1655
02:00:22,673 --> 02:00:24,133
So?

1656
02:00:25,968 --> 02:00:27,177
So what?

1657
02:00:30,222 --> 02:00:32,683
I made one decision in my life
based on money.

1658
02:00:32,850 --> 02:00:35,811
And I swore
I would never do it again.

1659
02:00:38,397 --> 02:00:40,441
You're not doing it for the money.

1660
02:00:40,941 --> 02:00:43,444
- No?
- No.

1661
02:00:45,446 --> 02:00:47,990
You're doing it
for what the money says.

1662
02:00:49,408 --> 02:00:53,120
And it says what it says to any player
that makes big money.

1663
02:00:53,787 --> 02:00:55,539
That they're worth it.

1664
02:01:04,006 --> 02:01:05,716
What a dump.

1665
02:01:09,887 --> 02:01:12,222
I really wanted to win here.

1666
02:01:16,268 --> 02:01:18,812
I really did.

1667
02:01:21,315 --> 02:01:23,484
I think you won pretty big, Billy.

1668
02:01:24,318 --> 02:01:26,445
Pete, we lost.

1669
02:01:28,030 --> 02:01:30,616
We lost.

1670
02:01:30,783 --> 02:01:34,244
It's only been a few days.
Give yourself some time to get over it.

1671
02:01:34,411 --> 02:01:39,041
Man, I don't get over these things.
Ever.

1672
02:01:46,048 --> 02:01:49,718
Come with me to the video room.
I wanna show you something.

1673
02:01:51,470 --> 02:01:54,765
No, man,
I'm not up for film right now.

1674
02:01:56,016 --> 02:01:58,101
Come on. Seriously.

1675
02:01:58,268 --> 02:02:00,437
Come on, Billy. Come on.

1676
02:02:02,147 --> 02:02:03,273
The Visalia Oaks...

1677
02:02:03,440 --> 02:02:06,235
and our 240-pound catcher,
Jeremy Brown...

1678
02:02:06,401 --> 02:02:10,030
who, as you know,
is scared to run to second base.

1679
02:02:10,197 --> 02:02:11,990
This was in a game six weeks ago.

1680
02:02:12,574 --> 02:02:14,701
This guy's gonna start
with a fastball.

1681
02:02:14,868 --> 02:02:17,287
Jeremy's gonna take him
to deep center.

1682
02:02:19,456 --> 02:02:20,958
Here's what's interesting...

1683
02:02:21,124 --> 02:02:24,002
because Jeremy's gonna do
what he never does.

1684
02:02:24,169 --> 02:02:25,462
He's gonna go for it.

1685
02:02:25,629 --> 02:02:28,882
He's gonna round first
and he's gonna go for it.

1686
02:02:30,092 --> 02:02:31,385
Okay?

1687
02:02:34,680 --> 02:02:39,643
This is all of Jeremy's nightmares
coming to life.

1688
02:02:42,271 --> 02:02:45,524
- They're laughing at him.
- And Jeremy's about to find out why.

1689
02:02:48,694 --> 02:02:51,071
Jeremy's about to realize...

1690
02:02:52,531 --> 02:02:55,659
that the ball went 60 feet
over the fence.

1691
02:02:58,287 --> 02:03:01,915
He hit a home run
and didn't even realize it.

1692
02:03:31,904 --> 02:03:34,948
How can you not be romantic
about baseball?

1693
02:03:39,870 --> 02:03:42,789
- It's a metaphor.
- I know it's a metaphor.

1694
02:03:47,502 --> 02:03:48,879
Okay.

1695
02:03:52,966 --> 02:03:56,011
Pete, you're a good egg.

1696
02:03:59,431 --> 02:04:01,183
I'll call you.

1697
02:05:01,994 --> 02:05:05,580
<i>Hey, Dad, this is the song I told you
I'd record.</i>

1698
02:05:05,747 --> 02:05:08,458
<i>Please don't show it to anyone else.</i>

1699
02:05:08,625 --> 02:05:11,712
<i>Let me know if you change your mind
and stay in California.</i>

1700
02:05:11,878 --> 02:05:14,923
<i>If not, you're a really great dad.</i>

